6:
AAAAALK! I need you to pack me a 
lunch!
10: Huh? Why, are you going somewhere?
14:
Yup! I'm out of components, so I can't 
do any alchemical experiments.
16:
I've gotta go get some more before 
I die of boredom, and I figured if I'm 
gonna be out in the forest, I might as 
well have a picnic!
19:
Oh, all right. If you're okay with 
leftovers, I'll go toss something 
together for you.
22:
Works for me! Thanks, Alk!
...Oh! And make sure you pack enough
for all four of us!
26:
For all four of us? ...We were just 
thinking of heading out to a new 
world.
30:
Aw, that can wait a day, can't it? 
Your mind is most creative when it's 
at play, y'know! You've gotta have fun 
if you wanna get some ideas cookin' 
up there!
32:
Back me up, Stella! A picnic in the 
Garden of the Sprites totally sounds 
fun, right?
36: Yes, it does sound like a nice idea.
40:
See, Light? Stella wants to go! 
PIC! NIC! PIC! NIC! PIC! NIC!
44: Whew! This looks like a good spot!
49: F-finally... *pant* I can't feel my legs...
54:
Ahaha! Sorry, Alk! I guess I went a little 
overboard resource gathering.
59:
Let's go on a picnic, she said. It'll be 
FUN, she said... What've you got in 
here?! Rocks?!
64:
Alk has a point. Herbs shouldn't be 
that heavy.
69:
Oh, um... Ahaha...ha... You're a good 
guesser Alk! It's got r-rocks...
80:
W-well, yeah, but they're special 
rocks!
89:
I mean, alchemy was born of the 
desire to turn common metals into 
gold! Everything starts from iron, Alk!
92:
For a second there, you almost 
sounded like a real alchemist.
101:
Alchemy typically does not end in 
explosions.
105:
Sure it does! Experimentation is the 
most important part of science! Fail 
a lot, then fail better!
110:
That sounds great in theory, but I 
worry you won't blow up the whole 
village. You've already reduced half 
your room to cinders…
115:
It'll be fiiiiine! Besides, I haven't found 
any mushrooms yet, so there's not 
much I CAN do.
119:
Mushrooms? What about those red 
ones over there?
123:
What? But those are EVERYWHERE! See,
with alchemy, the rarer the inputs are, 
the cooler the end-product is.
127:
What exactly are you trying to make 
anyways?
130:
That's top secret! You'll have to wait 
and see!
134:
...Right. Well, if you ever need 
mushrooms, there's—
151:
Wow, I can't believe it! Look, guys, 
there's a mushroom man!
153:
Hey there, buddy! Have you ever 
heard of ALCHEMY?
162:
Okay, now just hold still while I—
Hey!
166:
This is the first time I've been on a 
picnic this exciting.
173:
WAAAAAIT! C'mon, just let me have a 
little piece—it'll grow back, right? For 
scienceee!
